Education training provisions Lot would cover all aspects of learning required to ensure staff in education have the skills and knowledge to continue to provide services to children and young people and where required, maintain registration with professional bodies.
 These would include, but are not exclusive to, areas of:
 -Learning and Teaching;
 -Health & Wellbeing;
 -Educational leadership, coaching, mentoring and facilitation;
 -Curriculum development;
 -Learning technologies;
 -Technician training;
 -Promoting positive behaviour;
 -Educational Psychology;
 -Award Bearing Courses/Qualifications;
 -MiS Support training.
 Please note, this list of courses are indicative of the types of courses that the Council may call off from this lot of the DPS. Suppliers who wish to join the DPS do not have to be able to supply all of these courses and may sign up if they provide training that may fall under the heading of this Lot.. Please see attached documentation for any further information.

This Lot covers a range of general and role-specific training to meet the learning requirements for staff competences across the Council. These would include, but are not exclusive to areas of:
 -First Aid.
 -Working safely at height; general training and specific equipment training, e.g. PASMA;
 -Manual Handling; objects and people;
 -Lone working;
 -Display Screen Equipment (DSE) assessor;
 -Asbestos awareness;
 -Health and safety for senior executives.
 Please note, this list of courses are indicative of the types of courses that the Council may call off from this lot of the DPS. Suppliers who wish to join the DPS do not have to be able to supply all of these courses and may sign up if they provide training that may fall under the heading of this Lot.. Please see attached documentation for any further information.
